      "section_title": "7.4.1 The Basic Gravity Equation",
      "introduction": "The basic gravity equation expresses bilateral trade as a function of the economic sizes of the two countries and the distance between them. It is typically estimated using ordinary least squares (OLS) on log-transformed data. The model's remarkable empirical success — explaining 60-80% of the variation in bilateral trade — has made it a workhorse of empirical trade analysis.",
